title: Pre-Bypass Filters
long_description: Designed to filter recirculating, non-cellular priming solutions for extracorporeal circuits, Filtertek's disposable Pre-bypass filters are available in 0.2 or 5 micron pore sizes. To ensure proper usage, flow direction arrows and flow restriction notes are molded into the housing.
product_details_materials_of_constructio:
Filter Material: 5 micron, Acrylic Copolymer Membrane 
Housing Material: Acrylic  

Biological Safety: Passes Class VI Testing 
Sterilization Compatibility: EtO
product_details_connections:
Type: Tubing 
Inlet: 1/2" Barbed 
Outlet: 3/8" Barbed
product_details_performance_data:
Bubble point: 2.5 psi min. 
Minimum flow rate: 1.14 LPM @ 2 psi 
Maximum Flow Rate: 2.46 LPM @ 10 psi 
Maximum Operating Pressure: 50 psi 
Priming volume: 100 mL 
Usability: Disposable  

Specifications are for pre-sterilized products and are subject to change without notice. Results in specific applications may vary. Filtertek recommends that end user confirm fitness in specific applications.

title: 17mm Filter
long_description: Designed for small volume HPLC, organic and aqueous sample preparation, and as part of intravenous drug delivery systems in the Healthcare Industry.
product_details_materials_of_constructio:
Filter Material: 0.2 micron, Acrylic Copolymer Membrane 
Housing Material: Acrylic  

Sterilization Compatibility: EtO
product_details_performance_data:
Bubble point: >10 PSI 
Minimum flow rate: >200 mL/min air flow 
Pressure rating: >75 PSI 
Usability: Disposable
product_details_packaging:
Standard Pack: 2,000 pcs/carton  

Specifications are for pre-sterilized products and are subject to change without notice. Results in specific applications may vary. Filtertek recommends that end user confirm fitness in specific applications.

title: 17mm Filter
long_description: Designed for air or gas venting and filtration in applications such as transducer protection. Filtertek's 17mm  hydrophobic filters are available with tubing or luer lock connections for various applications.
product_details_materials_of_constructio:
Filter Material: 0.2 micron, Acrylic Copolymer Membrane 
Housing Material: Acrylic  

Biological Safety: USP Class VI Materials 
Sterilization Compatibility: EtO
product_details_performance_data:
Minimum flow rate: >200 mL/min @ 1.0 psi 
Pressure rating: >75 PSI 
Water entry pressure: >20 PSI 
Hold up volume: < 60 micro liter (with air purge) 
Usability: Disposable
product_details_packaging:
Standard Pack: 2,000 pcs/carton  

Specifications are for pre-sterilized products and are subject to change without notice. Results in specific applications may vary. Filtertek recommends that end user confirm fitness in specific applications.

title: Large Inline Filter
long_description: Designed for use in a number of different applications, these products are available in various screen sizes and port configurations. The robust housing design can withstand higher pressure situations and is resistant to alcohol and fuel.
product_details_materials_of_constructio:
Filter Material: 65 micron, Polyester Woven Screen 
Housing Material: Acetal  

Biological Safety: NSF Food Safe Materials 
Drug/Fluid Compatibility: Various Liquid, Fuel, Gas, Air
product_details_connections:
Type: Tubing 
Inlet: for 1/4" id hose or tubing Barbed 
Outlet: for 1/4" id hose or tubing Barbed
product_details_design:
Overall Dimensions: 1.12" major diameter x 4.00" long 
Effective Filtration Area: 7.59 in2
product_details_performance_data:
Maximum Operating Pressure: 100 psi 
Usability: Reusable
product_details_packaging:
Standard Pack: 550 pieces per carton  

Specifications are for pre-sterilized products and are subject to change without notice. Results in specific applications may vary. Filtertek recommends that end user confirm fitness in specific applications.

title: MediPure  I.V. Filter
long_description: Filtertek's self-priming Adult I.V. filters are designed to provide the safety, reliability, and efficiency that characterize superior patient care. Available in 0.2,1.2,Hiflo, and positively charged versions. Socket port versions are also available for external connection to I.V. tubing.
product_details_materials_of_constructio:
Filter Material: 0.2 micron, PES Membrane 
Vent Media: .02 micron, ePTFE Membrane 
Housing Material: Acrylic  

Biological Safety: USP Class VI Materials 
Sterilization Compatibility: Gamma Radiation, EtO
product_details_connections:
Type: Tubing 
Inlet: 0.120" od Male Slip 
Outlet: 0.120" od Male Slip
product_details_design:
Overall Dimensions: 2.86x1.27x0.15"height (0.526" at port) 
Effective Filtration Area: 12.0 cm2 
IP: Patent Pending
product_details_performance_data:
Bubble point: >45 psi 
Minimum flow rate: 25 mL/min @ 36" H2O head height 
Maximum Operating Pressure: 45 psi 
Prime time: 2.90 sec. @ 36" H2O head height 
Priming volume: 2.67 mL 
Bacterial retention: Passes 96hr test for bacterial retention 
Hold up volume: 0.92 mL 
Usability: Disposable
product_details_packaging:
Standard Pack: 500 parts/carton (bulk, non-sterile)  

Specifications are for pre-sterilized products and are subject to change without notice. Results in specific applications may vary. Filtertek recommends that end user confirm fitness in specific applications.
